result.execSummary:
The defendant Justin W. Zastrow was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Justin W. Zastrow in court with attorney John M. Bliss. David R. Knaapen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
11:15 a.m.  Court calls the case. 

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of:  Counts 2 & 3 - NO CONTEST

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty Counts 2 & 3.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.
Counts 1 & 4 are dismissed and read-in. 

Atty Knaapen makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Bliss makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 

BY THE COURT:
Count 2 - 
Serve 90 days jail - STAYED -
Huber for work, counseling and any other reason the sheriff will allow. 
Placed on probation for 24 months, concurrent to any probation the defendant is currently serving: 

Count 3 - 
Serve 120 days jail, concurrent with Count 2 - STAYED -
Huber for work, counseling and any other reason the sheriff will allow. 
Placed on probation for 24 months, concurrent with Count 2 and concurrent to any probation the defendant is currently serving: 

CONDITIONS:
Maintain absolute sobriety. 
Maintain employment. 
Participate in any other assessment or counseling deemed appropriate by the agent which may include a domestic abuse program if available and agent recommends. 
Pay costs including the DNA Surcharge and Domestic Abuse surcharge on each count
Provide DNA sample. 
No abusive Contact with Kirstie McCullough.

State files Information.
Defendant received copy of information.
Defendant waives reading of information. 

BY THE COURT:
NOT GUILTY Plea(s) entered.

Bond Continued.
